
== VS === 
Floating point problems with JavaScript floating points internal representation (64 bit - IEEE 754 standard)

In Javascript 0.1 + 0.2 is 0.30000000000000004

so

0.1 + 0.2 === 0.3    // false 

9007199254740992 + 1 // is equal to 9007199254740992  
9007199254740992 + 2 // is equal to 9007199254740994

SOLUTION: 
            toFixed() 
            toPrecision() 
